						<h1>Moving Resources - Movers&rsquo; Associations</h1>
					  <h2>U. S. and Regional</h2>
						<ul class="bl">
							<li><b><a href="www.moving.org/ " target="_new">AMSA</a></b> (American Moving &amp; Storage Association). The U.S. national trade association for the moving industry. Represents 3,500 moving companies and suppliers. Headquartered in Alexandria, Virginia.</li>
							<li><b><a href="http://www.missourimovers.org/" target="_new">MMA</a></b> Missouri Movers Association, Inc. The Missouri Movers Association is a trade association representing over 75 movers in Missouri since 1977. Our number one goal: Positive consumer move experiences. To support our mission MMA provides several useful links and consumer friendly tools for your use while planning a move.</li>						
							<li><b><a href="http://www.fmwa.org/" target="_new">FMWA</a></b> (Florida Movers and Warehousemen's Association). Founded in 1979.</li>
							<li><b><a href="http://www.imawa.com/" target="_new">IMAWA</a></b> (Illinois Movers and Warehousemen's Association). Springfield IL.</li>
						</ul>
						<h2>International Organizations</h2>
						<ul class="bl">
							<li><b><a href="http://www.fiata.com/" target="_new">FIATA</a></b> - F&eacute;d&eacute;ration Internationale des Associations de Transitaires et Assimil&eacute;s (International Federation of Freight Forwarders Associations)</li>
							<li><b><a href="http://www.fidi.com/" target="_new">FIDI</a></b> The International Federation of International Movers (F&eacute;d&eacute;ration Internationale des D&eacute;m&eacute;nageurs Internationaux), is a global organisation representing fully qualified professional international moving companies around the world.</li>
							<li><b><a href="http://www.iamovers.org/" target="_new">HHGFAA</a></b> (Household Goods Forwarders Association of America). Non-profit trade association. Worldwide membership of 2,000 companies in the U.S. and over 170 countries. Recently changed name to the International Association of Movers (IAM).</li>
							<li><b><a href="http://www.iamovers.org/" target="_new">IAM</a></b> (International Association of Movers) formerly HHGFAA. A non-profit global trade association representing over 2000 quality movers and related service providers in over 170 countries worldwide. Founded 1962, Headquarters office in Washington, DC.</li>
							<li><b><a href="http://www.iata.org/" target="_new">IATA</a></b> (The International Air Transport Association) is an international trade organization of airlines headquartered in Montreal, Quebec, Canada.</li>
							<li><b><a href="http://www.isaship.org/" target="_new">ISA</a></b> (International Shippers Association) Cooperative buying group for international movers. Affliated with HHGFAA and IAM. Headquartered in Washington DC</li>
							<li><b><a href="http://www.lacmassoc.org/" target="_new">LACMA</a></b> (Latin American &amp; Caribbean International Movers Association) represents professional movers from Latin America, the Caribbean, United States, Canada, Europe, Australia, Middle East and Far East.</li>
							<li><b><a href="https://www.omnimoving.com/forum/" target="_new">OMNI</a></b> (Overseas Moving Network International).</li>
							<li><b><a href="http://www.paima.com/" target="_new">PAIMA</a></b> (Pan American International Movers Association) includes list of members, company objectives, board of directors, member application, and convention registration.</li>
						</ul>
